I clean my teeth after the dinner
I walk around at 9 every evening
I run for my health every morning
I play games for two hours everyday
I sometimes read a book in the evening
I play football at weekends
I often ride my bike with my friends in daytime
I normally go to bed late


--> A day as an Mechanical Engineer:
I wake up at seven in the morning on weekdays.
I wash my face, after that I prepare/make a sandwich for eating at work at half past seven (at work = at the office)
I wait for the bus hours. When the bus comes, I get on the bus to get work
I work as a Senior Mechanical Design Engineer. I will be at the office at eight. I get to my desk and i turn on my computer
After that, I start to design tools that will take a few hours except my breaks
I design some steel materials such as Rolling-element bearing, Bolt, Shaft through Surface Modelling for making an engine
I sometimes participate in daily meetings with other engineers and managers. We talk about tasks to do and tools to design in the day
After that, I have lunch at half past one. After the lunch, I keep designing tools through Siemens NX on my computer until four or five pm
I get back home at half past five. 


--> A day as a Pre-School Teacher:
I usually wake up at seven. I have breakfast at half past seven or eight.
Actually I like having breakfast but I haven't much time so I eat it fast.
After breakfast I brush my teeth and I wear my clothes. Then, I go to school
My work starts at nine at school. Children come little by little. 
When all the children come to the class, I start with an Ice Breaker game.
We make a circle and one of the children starts to talk about a chosen topic.
Children ask some questions to each other and keep talking in order about the topic.
After the circle activity, I keep doing several different activities with children.
I prepare some reports about children on daily topics and activities at the end of the day, 
I share the reports with their parents. 


--> A day as an Academician in Economics:
I wake up at six every morning. I always wash my face and hands and brush my teeth.
I have breakfast at seven every morning. 
I leave home at eight on weekdays to get to the faculty
I generally get to the faculty by my car.
My lessons start at nine and end at noon
I normally go to the campus social facility to have lunch at half past twelve
After that, I get to my room in the faculty and start writing an article at one
I drink coffee and do a literature review to prepare for other lesson at two
I look at the current economic news and comments until half past two
I sometimes draw and analyze graphs from the data I find on exchange rates
I usually look at the data from central banks of various countries such as Turkey, England, America, Germany  
Especially, I pay attention to the data of the World Bank 
I examine the graphs of those banks and make comments
I occasionally answer student's questions at half past four
Later on, I leave from the faculty to get home at six
When I get home, I prepare dinner at seven
and then, I read the economy comments on social media for a while
I generally talk with my friends on Whatsapp or Instagram in the evening
in meantime, I keep writing articles until ten
I spend some time for myself to rest, and then I fall asleep close to midnight 




--> Self -Intro Of A Mechanical Engineer
I study Mechanical engineering
I live in Aksaray. I am from Ankara
Sometimes I go to Ankara to see with my family. My family live in Ankara
my dad is a farmer in Beypazarı
my mum is a housewife
I have five siblings
I want to live in Aksaray alone.
I design surface modelling works through SOLIDWORKS and AUTOCAD drawing
but I want to improve myself about other drawing programmes
I believe that I will be successful for the job
as my first internship, I completed my production internship in Park Termik
	I worked on the design of parts related to mining machinery
as my second internship, I have experience on railway system in VA-KO Vagon
	I was in charge of the control of incoming railway system parts
I go to university regularly and I visit the library
	because I study hard to graduate from the university nowadays

	Daily Activies:
	I always wake up at 8 
	I brush my teeth
	I sometimes go to the english course
	I get back home after the course
	I have dinner 
	I like playing the games
	I like playing war or strategic games
	I read a little before I sleep
	
--> Self-Intro of a Food Technician
	I work as a food technician in a factory
	I graduated from Food Technology in Selçuk University in 2019
	I completed my first and second internship as a food technician in a Chemistry Lab
	I am charge of food quality and control in the factory. Usually I analyze food chemically



Example:
Some of my friends think I have a boring daily routine, but I like it.  
I usually get up at about 6:00 or 6:30 in the morning, after my alarm clock wakes me up.    
First, I brush my teeth, and shave, and wash my face.  
Then, I get dressed and go downstairs to have breakfast with my family. 
I always have coffee, cereal, and lots of fruit.  That’s me in the picture with my wife.  
I take a bus to work because I don’t like to drive, 
and I always arrive at my office before 8:00.  I’m never late for work.  
Five o’clock is my favorite time of the day because I finish work 
and go home and see my wife and two children again.  
We eat dinner together in our dining room at around 6:00, 
and after that I hang out with my wife and kids at home.  
We really enjoy watching our favorite TV programs together, but two or three times a week   
I do exercise in the evening, so I can stay strong and healthy.  
This is very important!  Finally, at about 9:30, I go to bed, read for a while, 
and then fall asleep. Sure, some people think my daily routine is a little boring – 
but on weekends and holidays I love to fly airplanes for fun! 




---> HOUSE LIFE
roof
	--> on the roof -- çatıda
window
	--> out of the window	- pencereden dışarı
kitchen
	--> in the kitchen	- mutfakta
	--> on the table	- masada
	--> in the oven		- fırında
	--> in the fridge	- buzdolabında
wall
	--> on the wall		- duvarda
	--> next to the wall	- duvarın yanında
floor
	--> on the first floor	- birinci katta 
	--> on the second floor	- ikinci katta
	--> on the third floor	- üçüncü katta
	--> on the fourth floor - dördüncü katta
door
	--> at the door			- kapıda
	--> in front of the door	- kapının önünde
	--> behind the door		- kapının arkasında
stairs - basamaklar
	--> go upstairs		- yukarı çık
	--> go downstairs	- aşağı in
bathroom
	--> in shower		- duşta
bedroom
	--> on the bed		- yatağın üzerinde
	--> in bed		- yatakta
	--> get out of bed	- yataktan kalkmak
	--> under the bed	- yatağın altında
living room
	--> on the couch	- kanepede
	--> on the sofa		- koltukta
	--> on the television	- televizyonda
garden
	--> in the garden	- bahçede
garage
	--> in the garage	- garajda
	--> in the basement	- bodrumda


